WEBVTT

00:03.320 --> 00:05.062
(sighs)

00:05.064 --> 00:06.897
Huh?

00:06.899 --> 00:08.899
Stupid old couch.

00:08.901 --> 00:11.084
Aah! What the...

00:11.086 --> 00:13.262
(screaming)

00:15.424 --> 00:16.498
(grunts)

00:16.500 --> 00:17.725
(groans softly)

00:19.428 --> 00:21.094
Hmm.

00:21.096 --> 00:24.398
I always wondered
what was down here.

00:27.028 --> 00:29.436
You weren't worth
the trouble up there,

00:29.438 --> 00:32.089
and you aren't worth
the trouble down here.

00:32.091 --> 00:33.532
-MAN: Homer.
-Huh?

00:33.534 --> 00:34.758
It's me, kiddo.

00:34.760 --> 00:35.850
The Mick.

00:35.852 --> 00:37.761
My Mickey Mantle rookie card.

00:37.763 --> 00:39.780
The greatest treasure
of my youth.

00:39.782 --> 00:41.098
I'm still in mint condition.

00:41.100 --> 00:42.266
-Huh?
-Do you know how rare...

00:42.268 --> 00:44.434
-Aah!
-HOMER: Mm.

00:44.436 --> 00:45.544
My Rubik's Cube!

00:45.546 --> 00:47.695
The greatest treasure
of my youth.

00:47.697 --> 00:49.790
Let's see here.

00:49.792 --> 00:51.091
(grunting)

00:52.961 --> 00:55.128
No-good pile of garbage!

00:55.130 --> 00:57.631
MALE VOICE:
Not the first time
I've heard that.

00:57.633 --> 00:58.757
Ha!

00:58.759 --> 01:00.375
(gasps)
I know that voice.

01:01.062 --> 01:04.805
ALF. Oh, ALF,
you were canceled too soon.

01:04.807 --> 01:07.974
No, Homer, I was canceled
at exactly the right time.

01:07.976 --> 01:09.717
MARGE:
Homer.

01:09.719 --> 01:11.070
Homer, where are you?

01:11.072 --> 01:13.405
Darn.
I guess I should go.

01:13.407 --> 01:15.132
Go? Ha!

01:15.134 --> 01:16.983
You're part of the couch now.

01:16.985 --> 01:18.468
ALL:
Part of the couch.

01:18.470 --> 01:21.655
-Aah!
-The key to solving me
is patience.

01:21.657 --> 01:22.897
Never!

01:22.899 --> 01:23.916
-(panting)
-(snarling)

01:23.918 --> 01:24.917
(yells)

01:24.919 --> 01:25.992
(grunts)

01:25.994 --> 01:27.160
(whimpering)

01:27.162 --> 01:29.830
(snarling, hissing)

01:29.832 --> 01:31.256
(whimpering, grunts)

01:31.258 --> 01:32.833
MARGE:
What is this thread?

01:32.835 --> 01:34.635
This couch is falling apart.

01:35.763 --> 01:37.262
Hmm.

01:37.264 --> 01:38.155
(grunts)

01:38.157 --> 01:39.581
(yelling)

01:39.583 --> 01:40.657
(grunts)

01:40.659 --> 01:42.843
(snarling, groaning)

01:42.845 --> 01:44.161
(panting)

01:44.163 --> 01:45.920
-(grunts loudly)
-Whoa.

01:45.922 --> 01:48.590
Home again, safe and sound.

01:48.592 --> 01:49.591
(meows)

01:49.593 --> 01:51.026
Hey, knock it off.

01:52.762 --> 01:53.837
Aah!

01:53.839 --> 01:55.989
♪

02:00.362 --> 02:02.538
("Requiem in D Minor"
by Mozart playing)

02:11.799 --> 02:14.007
(indistinct chatter)

02:14.802 --> 02:17.194
(gasps) It's a fire!

02:17.196 --> 02:18.637
(gasps) Oh, my God, oh, my God!

02:18.639 --> 02:20.213
At the Flanders'.

02:20.215 --> 02:22.307
Flanders? Go back to sleep.

02:24.961 --> 02:26.979
Ned, what's wrong?

02:26.981 --> 02:28.796
(chuckles) I don't know.

02:28.798 --> 02:30.798
Guess God just loves to test me.

02:30.800 --> 02:32.192
Oh, look, here comes a truck.

02:33.562 --> 02:36.155
Lord, thank you for this tree
that I'm about to hit.

02:41.495 --> 02:43.662
("It's Bad You Know"
by R.L. Burnside playing)

02:50.320 --> 02:52.562
I found a pregnancy test.

02:52.564 --> 02:53.463
Yay!

02:54.566 --> 02:55.674
(sizzles)

02:59.996 --> 03:01.405
How you doin'?

03:01.407 --> 03:03.307
♪

03:08.004 --> 03:09.354
(hisses)

03:09.356 --> 03:12.265
Ned Flanders,
is everything okay?

03:12.267 --> 03:14.100
Well, let's just say
I may be okily,

03:14.102 --> 03:16.695
but I'm definitely not dokily.

03:16.697 --> 03:17.738
(alarm chirps)

03:18.941 --> 03:20.440
Aw. Dang it.

03:21.535 --> 03:25.370
(gasps) You've got
to tell someone what's wrong.

03:25.372 --> 03:28.281
Maybe we can discuss it
right now over cocoa.

03:28.283 --> 03:30.934
Sure. Just let me get the mail.

03:30.936 --> 03:32.085
Aah!

03:36.291 --> 03:39.033
(sniffles) Do you ever
question your life, Marge?

03:39.035 --> 03:40.944
You ever say, "What's the point
of going to church

03:40.946 --> 03:41.945
this Tuesday?"

03:41.947 --> 03:43.871
-What?
-Sorry, sorry.

03:43.873 --> 03:46.058
I've been going through
a lot of stress.

03:46.060 --> 03:48.143
Losing my hair
where it counts most.

03:49.654 --> 03:51.563
(gasps) A postiche.

03:51.565 --> 03:53.899
That's right.
It converts to eyebrows.

03:53.901 --> 03:57.069
It all started back when
I was briefly Bart's teacher.

03:57.071 --> 03:58.812
You were Bart's teacher?

03:58.814 --> 03:59.905
Oh, yes, I was.

03:59.907 --> 04:00.906
You can look it up.

04:00.908 --> 04:02.741
C, A, D, F, 12.

04:02.743 --> 04:04.910
Those were his grades
and the days he was absent.

04:04.912 --> 04:07.079
C, A, D, F, 12.

04:07.081 --> 04:09.823
Geez,
I really don't recall that.

04:09.825 --> 04:11.733
Well, that job
meant something to me.

04:11.735 --> 04:13.493
It-it-it truly did.

04:13.495 --> 04:14.811
Anyway, one day...

04:14.813 --> 04:16.646
<i> This was right before</i>
<i> the Supreme Court</i>

04:16.648 --> 04:17.923
<i> ignored the Constitution</i>

04:17.925 --> 04:20.408
<i> and blessedly let God</i>
<i> back in the schools.</i>

04:20.410 --> 04:23.077
Class, with all the troubles
in the world today, uh,

04:23.079 --> 04:24.596
I'd like you to pause
and take a moment

04:24.598 --> 04:26.840
of silent contemplation.

04:26.842 --> 04:29.676
Teacher, who should I pray to?

04:29.678 --> 04:32.329
<i> FLANDERS:</i>
<i> Don't say Jesus.</i>
<i> Don't say Jesus.</i>

04:32.331 --> 04:33.921
Jesus.
Pray to Jesus.

04:33.923 --> 04:35.107
Okay, pal, hold it right there.

04:35.109 --> 04:37.000
This is a public school.

04:37.002 --> 04:40.428
No trying to save<i> sinners!</i>

04:40.430 --> 04:41.363
Uh, y-yes, sir.

04:42.449 --> 04:44.449
Are you praying
for my soul right now?

04:44.451 --> 04:47.786
-I am.
-That is the one and only thing

04:47.788 --> 04:49.346
I can punish you for.

04:49.348 --> 04:50.330
Get out!

04:59.358 --> 05:01.374
Get out and stay out!

05:01.376 --> 05:02.542
God loves you.

05:02.544 --> 05:04.194
Nobody loves Willie!

05:05.121 --> 05:08.122
<i> FLANDERS: (sniffles)</i>
<i> I'd lost two wives, two jobs.</i>

05:08.124 --> 05:11.143
<i> I desperately needed to hit</i>
<i> the pews and talk to the Lord,</i>

05:11.145 --> 05:13.795
<i> but, uh, no such luck.</i>

05:13.797 --> 05:16.106
♪

05:23.048 --> 05:25.048
<i> Then I saw a Catholic church.</i>

05:25.050 --> 05:26.566
<i> Normally not a kneeler,</i>

05:26.568 --> 05:29.244
<i> but, uh,</i>
<i> beggars can't be choosers.</i>

05:32.315 --> 05:34.891
Can I help you, my friend?

05:34.893 --> 05:37.652
What brings you here
in such agita?

05:37.654 --> 05:39.563
Oh, nothing
you haven't heard before.

05:39.565 --> 05:42.156
Out of work.
Single father with two boys

05:42.158 --> 05:44.301
full of mischief and mayhem.

05:46.180 --> 05:48.213
Did you just blink?

05:48.215 --> 05:49.556
No.

05:52.094 --> 05:53.852
Maybe I could help you.

05:53.854 --> 05:56.262
I'm always looking
for new opportunities.

05:56.264 --> 05:58.506
I could be--
what do they call it--

05:58.508 --> 06:00.842
your angel investor.

06:00.844 --> 06:02.085
(laughing)

06:02.087 --> 06:03.695
My associates,

06:03.697 --> 06:06.365
Mr. Rude and Dr. Jerkov.

06:06.367 --> 06:09.684
-Whoa.
-Whoa! Look at me, I'm a doctor.

06:09.686 --> 06:10.927
(growls)

06:10.929 --> 06:13.688
Now, what is it that you do?

06:13.690 --> 06:15.281
I sell left-handed merchandise.

06:15.283 --> 06:18.025
You don't say.
I was left-handed myself

06:18.027 --> 06:21.213
until the nuns
beat it out of me.

06:21.215 --> 06:23.698
Perhaps you and I
could go into business together.

06:23.700 --> 06:27.052
I back your store
and you show your appreciation

06:27.054 --> 06:28.553
at a later date.

06:28.555 --> 06:30.037
This date may never come,

06:30.039 --> 06:31.965
but, actually, it will.

06:31.967 --> 06:34.559
And surprisingly soon.

06:34.561 --> 06:36.119
Won't you accept help

06:36.121 --> 06:38.138
from a sinister source?

06:38.140 --> 06:39.305
Well, I...
(gasps)

06:39.307 --> 06:41.942
"Sinister"
meaning "left-handed."

06:43.052 --> 06:45.295
Well, sir,
you seem like a godly man,

06:45.297 --> 06:47.297
and I'm a wee bit desperate.

06:47.299 --> 06:49.649
Let me do my due diligence
and get back to you.

06:49.651 --> 06:52.202
You do your due.

06:54.473 --> 06:57.732
You went into business
with the Mob?

06:57.734 --> 06:58.825
I googled him.

06:58.827 --> 07:00.252
It said "legitimate business."

07:00.254 --> 07:02.328
I never dreamed
the Internet would lie.

07:02.330 --> 07:04.831
Stupid, stupid, stupid Flanders.

07:04.833 --> 07:06.332
(groans)

07:06.334 --> 07:09.136
At first, it was
too good to be true.

07:14.601 --> 07:16.826
Buy the scissors.

07:16.828 --> 07:18.161
But I'm right-handed.

07:18.163 --> 07:20.847
-How'd you like to be no-handed?
-Mm.

07:20.849 --> 07:23.608
<i> FLANDERS:</i>
<i> In my new Leftorium,</i>
<i> all was right.</i>

07:23.610 --> 07:25.760
<i> And I did something</i>
<i> I hadn't done in, uh,</i>

07:25.762 --> 07:27.170
<i> I don't know how long.</i>

07:27.172 --> 07:29.189
<i> God help me, I smiled.</i>

07:30.117 --> 07:32.692
Flanders is in trouble
with the Mob.

07:32.694 --> 07:34.453
Finally, he does something cool.

07:34.455 --> 07:37.530
Ned, no offense, but how could
you get mixed up with Fat Tony?

07:37.532 --> 07:39.958
I mean, that sounds
like something<i> I</i> would do.

07:39.960 --> 07:41.293
(laughs)

07:41.295 --> 07:42.610
(chuckling)

07:42.612 --> 07:43.628
You're right.

07:43.630 --> 07:45.371
(laughing)

07:45.373 --> 07:46.998
Homer is stupid, all right.

07:47.000 --> 07:49.526
"PhD" is how he spells "food".

07:49.528 --> 07:50.694
(laughs)

07:50.696 --> 07:51.953
(giggling)

07:51.955 --> 07:53.546
(laughing)

07:53.548 --> 07:55.122
(chuckling)

07:55.124 --> 07:56.382
(barking laugh)

07:56.384 --> 07:58.793
All right, I'm stupid.
That's enough.

07:58.795 --> 08:00.061
Eh, it's funny.
(chuckles)

08:04.893 --> 08:07.301
It's true--
I do trust everyone I meet.

08:07.303 --> 08:10.280
But I did ask
some probing questions.

08:12.400 --> 08:15.218
<i> Buona fortuna.</i>
Things are good?

08:15.220 --> 08:16.828
Uh, little too good.

08:16.830 --> 08:18.571
So, I must ask, uh,

08:18.573 --> 08:20.406
are you a good fella?

08:20.408 --> 08:21.482
A goodfella?

08:21.484 --> 08:23.076
Indeed I am.

08:23.078 --> 08:25.987
And I heard you're a wise guy.

08:25.989 --> 08:27.747
Some call me such.

08:27.749 --> 08:29.582
I have to run an errand.

08:29.584 --> 08:31.134
Come with me.

08:33.997 --> 08:36.139
♪

08:38.760 --> 08:40.760
You're a little light.

08:40.762 --> 08:42.595
(gasps)
Take-a my hat.

08:42.597 --> 08:44.597
Take-a my second hat.

08:44.599 --> 08:46.082
Uh, take-a my bald wig.

08:46.084 --> 08:47.433
(panting)

08:48.362 --> 08:51.363
Ooh, if I knew that
mobsters like Italian food,

08:51.365 --> 08:53.423
I would have-a stuck
to the sushi.

08:53.425 --> 08:55.759
I used to cut-uh the fish
and make-uh the rice

08:55.761 --> 08:57.944
and serve-uh the fish
and chop-uh the thing.

08:57.946 --> 09:00.354
They took me in
as one of their own.

09:00.356 --> 09:03.099
♪<i> The record shows</i> ♪

09:03.101 --> 09:05.435
♪<i> We took the blows</i> ♪

09:05.437 --> 09:08.454
♪<i> And, Lord, we did it Thy</i> ♪

09:08.456 --> 09:11.624
♪<i> Way.</i> ♪

09:11.626 --> 09:12.717
(song ends)

09:12.719 --> 09:15.628
-This guy.
-This guy.

09:15.630 --> 09:17.630
No, this guy.

09:17.632 --> 09:18.798
Am I right?

09:18.800 --> 09:20.967
I used to be this guy.

09:20.969 --> 09:23.878
<i> FLANDERS:</i>
<i>We had some of the most intimate</i>
<i> and vague conversations</i>

09:23.880 --> 09:25.121
<i> I've ever been a part of.</i>

09:25.123 --> 09:28.733
So, did that thing go down
with our friend?

09:28.735 --> 09:32.462
If you replace "that thing"
with "ice pick,"

09:32.464 --> 09:35.465
"our friend"
with "Benny the Barber"

09:35.467 --> 09:38.577
and "down"
with "into his eyeball,"

09:38.579 --> 09:40.662
you may have your answer.

09:42.307 --> 09:43.973
Did I miss anything?

09:43.975 --> 09:45.992
We've been talking
about a lot of murders.

09:45.994 --> 09:48.253
Eh, I mean, nothing.

09:49.998 --> 09:51.906
-(knocking)
-Something wrong, T?

09:51.908 --> 09:53.925
Business difficulties.

09:53.927 --> 09:55.927
(grunting)

09:55.929 --> 09:58.822
Time for another IKEA run.

09:58.824 --> 09:59.931
Want to talk about it?

09:59.933 --> 10:02.992
You know, I will talk about it.
To you.

10:02.994 --> 10:04.769
I have many operations.

10:04.771 --> 10:08.331
One of those is, um,
selling medicine

10:08.333 --> 10:11.943
to, um, patients
on the street, as it were.

10:11.945 --> 10:13.094
Aw.

10:13.096 --> 10:15.096
But a rival, shall we say,

10:15.098 --> 10:17.282
pharmacist from New Jersey

10:17.284 --> 10:20.360
is trying
to put the squeeze on me.

10:20.362 --> 10:21.769
We may have to

10:21.771 --> 10:23.771
go to the mattresses.

10:23.773 --> 10:26.182
Well, a healthy night's sleep
is always important,

10:26.184 --> 10:27.626
but I think
you'd feel a lot better

10:27.628 --> 10:31.688
if you did a few exercises from
this, uh, self-esteem workbook.

10:31.690 --> 10:33.206
<i> Che diavolo!</i>

10:33.208 --> 10:36.693
See, you can pencil your way out
of your "maze of miseries,"

10:36.695 --> 10:38.970
draw a little frowny face
for self-expression.

10:38.972 --> 10:40.621
Come on, you know you wanna.

10:40.623 --> 10:41.789
I don't wanna.

10:41.791 --> 10:43.308
(singsongy):
Yes, you do.

10:43.310 --> 10:46.561
All right, all right,
I'll draw the freakin' frown.

10:48.890 --> 10:50.315
What do you know.

10:50.317 --> 10:53.443
I actually feel better.

10:55.563 --> 10:58.990
(gasps) You just gave me
the kiss of death.

10:58.992 --> 11:00.233
(chuckles)

11:00.235 --> 11:01.826
And a pinch to grow an inch.

11:01.828 --> 11:03.662
(chuckling)

11:04.665 --> 11:07.891
<i> FLANDERS:</i>
<i> Then that wonderful summer</i>
<i> ended in a fall.</i>

11:07.893 --> 11:09.893
(humming a tune)

11:09.895 --> 11:12.653
She<i> walked in.</i>

11:12.655 --> 11:14.172
-What do you want?
-Hi.

11:14.174 --> 11:17.491
I'm selling band candy
and I only need 2,000 more boxes

11:17.493 --> 11:20.161
to go on a trip to Cincinnati
and then I'll be on my way.

11:20.163 --> 11:22.422
No trouble.
(chuckles nervously)

11:22.424 --> 11:23.682
Mr. Flanders?

11:23.684 --> 11:25.934
(quietly): Come with me.

11:26.836 --> 11:28.928
You, the best man on our block,

11:28.930 --> 11:31.338
accidentally joined
a criminal gang?

11:31.340 --> 11:33.692
Criminals? Criminals?!

11:33.694 --> 11:35.601
Oh, my God. (sighs)

11:35.603 --> 11:37.195
I see it all now.

11:37.197 --> 11:39.221
Well, you've
got to get out of there.

11:39.223 --> 11:42.200
So, Ned, who is this young lady
who has seen a lot

11:42.202 --> 11:44.427
and possibly too much?

11:44.429 --> 11:46.371
Just leave me alone,
Little Miss Busybody.

11:46.373 --> 11:48.206
I find a place
where I'm welcome,

11:48.208 --> 11:50.375
but you know
what's best for me.

11:50.377 --> 11:52.769
-I just meant...
-Well, maybe the real criminal

11:52.771 --> 11:55.362
is the neighbor who borrows
my stuff and never returns it.

11:55.364 --> 11:58.216
Your dad has
my garage door opener.

11:58.218 --> 12:00.793
-Why?
-Okay. Geez.

12:00.795 --> 12:03.054
Just trying to sell band candy.

12:03.056 --> 12:04.556
(quietly):
Put me down for a dozen.

12:04.558 --> 12:05.557
Now scoot.

12:05.559 --> 12:07.267
Oh...

12:08.228 --> 12:09.786
Um... (clears throat)
My friend,

12:09.788 --> 12:12.455
do you mind if I have a word
with you, uh, about, uh...

12:12.457 --> 12:13.456
Hell?

12:13.458 --> 12:16.809
Language.
You disrespect this photo,

12:16.811 --> 12:18.528
which I believe to be my mother.

12:20.298 --> 12:22.407
Well sir, I'll just
come right out and say it.

12:22.409 --> 12:25.660
You, my friend,
are a rotten tomato.

12:27.396 --> 12:29.730
Let me explain something to you.

12:29.732 --> 12:32.976
You have aligned yourself
with a secretive organization

12:32.978 --> 12:34.586
with many, many traditions

12:34.588 --> 12:37.146
we are not proud of.

12:37.148 --> 12:38.923
I know.
You're Catholic.

12:38.925 --> 12:40.407
You do not know.

12:40.409 --> 12:43.653
You have joined
"this thing of ours."

12:43.655 --> 12:44.787
What thing of yours?

12:44.789 --> 12:46.097
You know the thing.

12:46.099 --> 12:48.099
I don't know the thing.
You people are less direct

12:48.101 --> 12:49.509
than a corkscrew.

12:49.511 --> 12:50.843
-(whispering)
-What the...

12:50.845 --> 12:53.179
No.
Whackery?

12:53.181 --> 12:55.848
Well, as I told the people
at Equinox health clubs,

12:55.850 --> 12:58.109
no matter what I signed,
I want out.

12:58.111 --> 12:59.760
(phone dings)

12:59.762 --> 13:01.020
Oh!

13:01.022 --> 13:02.322
(grumbles)

13:03.432 --> 13:05.858
I'm afraid
from our association

13:05.860 --> 13:09.120
there is only one way out.

13:10.123 --> 13:12.606
Just checking--
uh, what floor are we on?

13:12.608 --> 13:14.775
First.

13:14.777 --> 13:16.443
FLANDERS:
I'll pay for the window!

13:16.445 --> 13:20.206
So, for safety, I sent
my boys to their grandpawpaw.

13:20.208 --> 13:23.526
And thank You, Lord,
for the macaroni and the cheese.

13:23.528 --> 13:26.195
And God bless the little strings
on our bananas.

13:26.197 --> 13:27.621
Oh, man, oh, man.

13:27.623 --> 13:30.883
How did my family tree
get such square roots?

13:30.885 --> 13:34.020
But as for me, I'm gonna
tough this out at home.

13:36.316 --> 13:39.025
♪

13:45.900 --> 13:47.992
Okay.
Time for plan B:

13:47.994 --> 13:49.702
asylum at the Church.

13:52.057 --> 13:54.907
Oh, dear God.

13:54.909 --> 13:56.726
Papa just got himself

13:56.728 --> 13:58.485
a new set of trains.

13:58.487 --> 14:04.050
("Musica Poetica II"
by Carl Orff playing)

14:16.356 --> 14:19.098
All right.
Let's see what we've got here.

14:19.100 --> 14:20.416
I-I don't know, Lou.

14:20.418 --> 14:23.027
That yellow tape clearly says,
"do not cross."

14:23.029 --> 14:25.196
Uh, that doesn't
apply to cops, Chief.

14:25.198 --> 14:28.283
I just want to know
where the hell is Ned Flanders.

14:34.115 --> 14:36.599
Now, Flanders, in the spirit
of neighborliness,

14:36.601 --> 14:39.785
you can hide
in our garage until, uh...

14:39.787 --> 14:41.212
how does Thursday sound?

14:41.214 --> 14:44.365
-Today's Thursday.
-You're welcome.

14:45.293 --> 14:48.945
Poor Ned. At least
my kids are safe. Sort of.

14:48.947 --> 14:51.631
-(grunts)
-Oh, yeah.
-Mmm.

14:51.633 --> 14:53.449
So, tough day at work?

14:53.451 --> 14:54.559
No chitchat.

14:57.546 --> 14:59.063
Where is he?

14:59.065 --> 15:01.399
-Where is who?
-You know who.

15:01.401 --> 15:03.459
I'm just a stupid nobody
who doesn't have any Flanders.

15:03.461 --> 15:05.795
I mean answers.
I mean answers about Flanders.

15:05.797 --> 15:08.131
You can't choke me from behind
if I'm standing in front of you.

15:08.133 --> 15:10.199
-(exclaiming)
-(grumbling)

15:11.077 --> 15:13.328
(sighs) Ooh.

15:14.489 --> 15:15.321
Oh.

15:15.323 --> 15:17.081
My friend, if you know something

15:17.083 --> 15:18.641
and withhold from us,

15:18.643 --> 15:21.068
it will not go well.

15:21.070 --> 15:22.403
Mmm. (whimpers)

15:22.405 --> 15:25.665
What he means is...
(imitates cutting) Oh, crap,

15:25.667 --> 15:27.300
my fingernails are too sharp!

15:28.244 --> 15:29.669
Aah! I can't see!

15:29.671 --> 15:31.095
(gangsters whimpering)

15:31.932 --> 15:33.264
Oh, you did good, Homer.

15:33.266 --> 15:36.434
You didn't stop them,
but you made them very mad.

15:42.258 --> 15:44.591
We got him now
as long as he don't look back.

15:44.593 --> 15:47.520
With that fat neck?
Fuhgeddaboudit.

15:47.522 --> 15:50.365
("Mud Island Chase"
by Dave Grusin playing)

16:08.451 --> 16:10.969
Oh, how many dinners
can this guy have?

16:10.971 --> 16:13.137
He eats more than
Frankie Eats Too Much.

16:13.139 --> 16:15.473
Our nicknames--
they're so judgmental.

16:15.475 --> 16:17.475
♪

16:32.066 --> 16:35.142
Oh. Oh, God. Oh God.
Where's Ned?

16:35.144 --> 16:36.719
I don't know.
I came back

16:36.721 --> 16:39.313
to bring him fresh towels
and he disappeared.

16:39.315 --> 16:41.165
He wouldn't just leave
without drying himself off.

16:41.167 --> 16:43.409
-He wouldn't!
-(gun chambers rack)

16:43.411 --> 16:45.061
No Flanders!

16:45.063 --> 16:47.730
And who knew fatso
had such a hot wife.

16:47.732 --> 16:49.232
Eh, it's a sitcom thing.

16:49.234 --> 16:51.567
<i> King of Queens,</i>
Fred Flintstone,

16:51.569 --> 16:52.844
Timmy and Lassie.

16:52.846 --> 16:54.328
Such a beautiful dog.

16:54.330 --> 16:58.057
Where the hell
would Flanders go?

17:11.865 --> 17:14.348
Well, this would be
a good time for a prayer.

17:14.350 --> 17:16.609
Let's see.

17:16.611 --> 17:19.929
May I suggest a prayer
from the Klingon Language Bible?

17:19.931 --> 17:23.432
(speaks Klingon)

17:23.434 --> 17:26.026
(sighs)
Even I think this is idiotic.

17:26.028 --> 17:27.628
Eh, good luck.

17:34.554 --> 17:36.128
Why are you here?

17:36.130 --> 17:40.058
Because, deep down, I believe
you are a good man, Fat Tony.

17:40.060 --> 17:42.209
The... Well, that's not
your Christian name.

17:42.211 --> 17:44.395
Let me call you... Anthony.

17:44.397 --> 17:46.046
Anthony.

17:46.048 --> 17:48.307
Mama used to call me that.

17:48.309 --> 17:50.217
Mm-hmm. And a man
who loves his mother

17:50.219 --> 17:52.570
as much as you do
can't be all bad.

17:53.965 --> 17:55.389
Mommy.

17:55.391 --> 17:58.242
And someone who bought
that much band candy

17:58.244 --> 18:00.894
must have a very soft heart.

18:00.896 --> 18:02.580
Maybe I like candy.

18:02.582 --> 18:03.989
You are right.

18:03.991 --> 18:07.159
I'm hard on the outside
and soft on the inside.

18:07.161 --> 18:10.329
Like the world's
most murderous cannoli.

18:10.331 --> 18:13.424
Knew it. Repeat after me:
I believe in God.

18:13.426 --> 18:15.760
I believe in God.

18:15.762 --> 18:17.336
The creator almighty.

18:17.338 --> 18:19.079
The creator
almighty.

18:19.081 --> 18:21.599
Maker of Heaven and Earth.

18:21.601 --> 18:23.326
Maker of Heaven
and Earth!

18:23.328 --> 18:25.344
And so on and so forth!

18:25.346 --> 18:27.087
(sobs)

18:28.166 --> 18:31.734
Now, take my hand
in loving friendship.

18:33.596 --> 18:35.262
Okay, kill him.

18:35.264 --> 18:37.097
-What?
-I'm sorry, Ned.

18:37.099 --> 18:39.358
But this is the business
we've chosen.

18:39.360 --> 18:41.543
Although you were
tricked into it.

18:41.545 --> 18:42.695
That's on me.

18:42.697 --> 18:45.181
Any last requests?

18:45.183 --> 18:46.791
Eh, just one.

18:46.793 --> 18:48.126
Can I remove my mustache?

18:48.128 --> 18:51.045
I... I want to be clean-shaven
for the Lord.

18:54.692 --> 18:56.359
He's wearin' a wire!
Aah!

18:56.361 --> 18:58.861
I told you
to pat down his schnozz!

18:58.863 --> 19:00.304
-(sirens wailing outside)
-(tires screech)

19:00.306 --> 19:02.473
(ice cream truck music playing)

19:04.960 --> 19:06.552
(music stops)

19:06.554 --> 19:10.297
This whole time,
you've been working for the G.

19:10.299 --> 19:11.816
Not the whole time.

19:11.818 --> 19:13.225
<i> But once a certain young lady</i>

19:13.227 --> 19:15.319
<i>pulled the wool from my eyes...</i>

19:16.381 --> 19:18.823
-I'd like to be a snitch.
-Okay.

19:18.825 --> 19:20.716
But if things go south
and we have to pull you out,

19:20.718 --> 19:23.477
you're gonna wind up
Mr. John Smith in Utah.

19:23.479 --> 19:25.830
Oh, that's a dream
I've always had.

19:25.832 --> 19:28.166
-(handcuffs click)
-I loved you, man.

19:28.168 --> 19:30.525
You didn't even
remember my birthday.

19:30.527 --> 19:31.744
I sent you a card.

19:31.746 --> 19:34.005
Belatedly.

19:38.511 --> 19:40.236
-Flanders.
-Simpson.

19:40.238 --> 19:42.071
I'm proud of you, man.

19:42.073 --> 19:43.756
I can't believe
someone in this town

19:43.758 --> 19:45.666
finally put that guy in jail.

19:45.668 --> 19:47.426
-Yeah.
-What's wrong?

19:47.428 --> 19:49.336
Well, I miss 'em a little.

19:49.338 --> 19:51.747
That guy can really kiss.

19:51.749 --> 19:55.059
Stupid Flanders,
you're a brave man.

19:55.061 --> 19:57.177
(short chuckle)
I'm nothing special.

19:57.179 --> 19:59.680
I take my shower in the dark
just like anybody else.

